{"id":"4301fcd3-9ae4-43d0-a990-e073989dee67","type":"decision","content":"3.5 chars-per-token ratio for token estimation. Reason: Conservative ratio that overestimates slightly (safer — avoids overflow on models with aggressive tokenizers). Real-world English text averages ~4 chars/token, code ~3 chars/token. 3.5 is a safe middle ground.","created_at":"2026-02-27T10:10:00Z","created_by":"session-harvest","session_id":"local-first-forge","context":{"prd_id":null,"story_id":null,"phase":null},"weight":0.5,"validation_count":0,"retrieval_count":0,"tags":["decision","session-harvest"],"reality_anchor":{"has_tests":false,"test_file":null,"test_passing":false},"lineage":{"parent_id":null,"supersedes":[],"superseded_by":null}}
{"id":"0930efb2-0597-462b-8ea3-44d202bbc787","type":"decision","content":"Keyword-based task classification, no LLM. Reason: Using an LLM to classify tasks for cost routing defeats the purpose (adds cost). Keyword matching is zero-cost, zero-latency, and deterministic. Complex tasks default to cloud (safety-first).","created_at":"2026-02-27T10:10:00Z","created_by":"session-harvest","session_id":"local-first-forge","context":{"prd_id":null,"story_id":null,"phase":null},"weight":0.5,"validation_count":0,"retrieval_count":0,"tags":["decision","session-harvest"],"reality_anchor":{"has_tests":false,"test_file":null,"test_passing":false},"lineage":{"parent_id":null,"supersedes":[],"superseded_by":null}}
{"id":"cd91e343-88c3-4420-9aa1-24e7663669d7","type":"decision","content":"60-second TTL for health check cache. Reason: Balance between responsiveness (detect server restart quickly) and avoiding per-turn latency. 60s means at most 1 health check per minute, and model servers typically stay up/down for minutes, not seconds.","created_at":"2026-02-27T10:10:00Z","created_by":"session-harvest","session_id":"local-first-forge","context":{"prd_id":null,"story_id":null,"phase":null},"weight":0.5,"validation_count":0,"retrieval_count":0,"tags":["decision","session-harvest"],"reality_anchor":{"has_tests":false,"test_file":null,"test_passing":false},"lineage":{"parent_id":null,"supersedes":[],"superseded_by":null}}
